WEBVTT

00:08.067 --> 00:09.502
<i>PREVIOUSLY ON "WEEDS"...</i>

00:09.535 --> 00:11.371
I THINK
I WAS A BAD PERSON.

00:11.404 --> 00:13.239
I DON'T WANT TO BE LIKE THAT
ANYMORE.

00:13.272 --> 00:14.307
OKAY. GOOD FOR YOU.

00:14.340 --> 00:16.409
NO.
GOOD FOR ALL OF US.

00:16.442 --> 00:17.210
S.E.C.?

00:17.812 --> 00:19.647
I'VE HEARD OF YOU GUYS.

00:19.681 --> 00:21.816
YEAH, YOU GUYS HAVE
THOSE FEDERAL PENSION PLANS

00:21.849 --> 00:23.518
TIED IN
WITH OUR MIDDAY FUND.

00:23.551 --> 00:25.553
IF WE GO DOWN,
YOU GO DOWN.

00:25.587 --> 00:26.554
WHAT ARE YOU GIRLS
DOING?

00:26.588 --> 00:28.156
PACKING UP.
GOING HOME.

00:28.189 --> 00:29.958
HOME? WHY?

00:29.991 --> 00:31.793
BECAUSE
THEY'RE GETTING BACK TOGETHER.

00:31.826 --> 00:33.695
DID SHE SAY THAT?
SHE SAID YOU WERE GOING HOME?

00:33.728 --> 00:34.696
YOU CAN'T GO.

00:34.729 --> 00:36.431
THE GIRLS CAN'T GO.

00:37.298 --> 00:38.700
[ GASPS ]

00:38.733 --> 00:41.202
I NO LONGER CHOOSE TO
EMBRACE ALL THAT YOU ARE, JILL.

00:41.236 --> 00:43.404
YOU NO LONGER HAVE
MY FUCKING TROTH!

00:43.438 --> 00:44.806
Shane:
I'M NOT IN COLLEGE.

00:44.839 --> 00:46.541
I'M IN THE POLICE ACADEMY.

00:46.574 --> 00:48.076
WE'RE CRIMINALS.
IT'S THE FAMILY BUSINESS.

00:48.109 --> 00:49.410
WHAT THE FUCK
ARE YOU DOING?

00:49.444 --> 00:50.778
I THINK
I WANT TO BE A COP.

00:50.812 --> 00:52.947
RED LINES ARE PEOPLE
WHO WANT YOU DEAD FOR REVENGE.

00:52.981 --> 00:54.616
AS YOU CAN SEE,
WE'RE MOSTLY RED.

00:54.649 --> 00:56.818
SHE'S SO GREAT
AT PISSING PEOPLE OFF.

00:56.851 --> 00:59.921
THINK HE'LL COME BACK,
TRY AND FINISH WHAT HE STARTED?

00:59.954 --> 01:01.956
I DON'T KNOW.
HOPE SO.

01:01.990 --> 01:03.825
GIVE ME A CHANCE
TO NAIL THE FUCKER.

01:11.032 --> 01:14.202
♪♪ LITTLE BOXES
ON THE HILLSIDE ♪♪

01:14.235 --> 01:17.605
♪♪ LITTLE BOXES
MADE OF TICKY‐TACKY! ♪♪

01:17.639 --> 01:20.742
♪♪ LITTLE BOXES
ON THE HILLSIDE ♪♪

01:20.775 --> 01:23.945
♪♪ LITTLE BOXES
ALL THE SAME! ♪♪

01:23.978 --> 01:27.215
♪♪ THERE'S A GREEN ONE
AND A PINK ONE ♪♪

01:27.248 --> 01:30.351
♪♪ A BLUE ONE
AND A YELLOW ONE ♪♪

01:30.385 --> 01:33.888
♪♪ AND THEY'RE ALL MADE
OUT OF TICKY‐TACKY! ♪♪

01:33.922 --> 01:37.625
♪♪ AND THEY ALL LOOK
JUST THE SAME ♪♪

01:37.659 --> 01:40.862
♪♪ AND THE PEOPLE
IN THE HOUSES ♪♪

01:40.895 --> 01:43.965
♪♪ ALL WENT TO
THE UNIVERSITY ♪♪

01:43.998 --> 01:47.135
♪♪ WHERE THEY WERE
PUT IN BOXES! ♪♪

01:47.168 --> 01:50.738
♪♪ AND THEY CAME OUT
ALL THE SAME! ♪♪

01:50.772 --> 01:53.942
♪♪ AND THERE'S DOCTORS
AND LAWYERS ♪♪

01:53.975 --> 01:57.245
♪♪ AND BUSINESS EXECUTIVES ♪♪

01:57.278 --> 02:00.682
♪♪ AND THEY'RE ALL MADE
OUT OF TICKY‐TACKY! ♪♪

02:00.715 --> 02:04.219
♪♪ AND THEY ALL LOOK
JUST THE SAME ♪♪

02:07.722 --> 02:08.723
Jill: MORNING!

02:08.756 --> 02:10.558
FIRST DAY BACK
ON DRY LAND?

02:10.592 --> 02:12.460
YOU NEED HELP,
OR YOU GOT IT?

02:12.493 --> 02:13.828
I GOT IT. THANKS.

02:13.861 --> 02:16.798
ARE YOU [CHUCKLES]
ON ROLLER SKATES?

02:16.831 --> 02:18.566
Andy: YEAH.
[ LAUGHS ]

02:18.600 --> 02:21.369
I'M, UH,
COACHING THE TWINS' DERBY TEAM.

02:21.402 --> 02:23.571
THEIR OLD COACH
LEFT HER FAMILY

02:23.605 --> 02:25.773
FOR SOME
FLORIDIAN FIRE DANCER,

02:25.807 --> 02:27.242
SO I'M STEPPING UP.

02:27.275 --> 02:28.676
AH.

02:28.710 --> 02:31.145
STEVIE'S PLAYING
WITH A FLYSWATTER?

02:31.179 --> 02:32.313
MY IDEA.

02:32.347 --> 02:35.917
HE'S BEEN OFF OF VIDEO GAMES
FOR ALMOST 27 MINUTES.

02:35.950 --> 02:38.086
OH. NICE WORK.
HI, STEVIE.

02:38.119 --> 02:38.953
OH, OH!

02:38.987 --> 02:40.154
THERE'S ONE
OVER THERE.

02:40.188 --> 02:41.222
HE STOLE MY WALLET.
GO GET HIM.

02:41.256 --> 02:42.657
[ CHUCKLES ]

02:42.690 --> 02:45.126
UM,
SHANE LEFT YOU THIS.

02:45.159 --> 02:47.962
WOW.

02:47.996 --> 02:52.467
AND I GOT YOU...
THESE.

02:52.500 --> 02:55.403
TRACTION SOCKS ‐‐
SO YOU DON'T SLIP.

02:55.436 --> 02:58.940
THEY SAY "POWER PAWS."

02:58.973 --> 03:02.410
OH, I MUST HAVE
GRABBED THE DOG ONES.

03:02.443 --> 03:04.812
WELL,
I WILL RETURN THEM.

03:04.846 --> 03:06.481
TARGET GIVES YOU
30 DAYS.

03:06.514 --> 03:07.615
OH, YEAH.

03:07.649 --> 03:09.684
THIS IS
THE RECEIPT DRAWER NOW.

03:09.717 --> 03:11.419
HEY!
MY GARLIC PRESS!

03:11.452 --> 03:12.620
Andy: YOU HUNGRY?

03:12.654 --> 03:14.322
WANT ME
TO MAKE YOU SOMETHING?

03:14.355 --> 03:15.690
EGGS FLORENTINE?
OSSO BUCO?

03:15.723 --> 03:16.925
OH, FORGET IT.

03:16.958 --> 03:18.393
EVERYTHING TASTES
LIKE BLACK LICORICE.

03:18.426 --> 03:20.028
STILL?

03:22.497 --> 03:24.933
EH, ECH.

03:24.966 --> 03:26.801
BUMMERS OF THE MIRACLES
OF THE BRAIN.

03:26.834 --> 03:28.603
Jill: ANYWAY, WHAT ELSE?
WHAT ELSE?

03:28.636 --> 03:31.639
OH, YOUR RECOVERY FOODS
ARE IN THE CRISPER.

03:31.673 --> 03:32.941
IT'S MOSTLY BLUEBERRIES.

03:32.974 --> 03:34.108
WebMD.

03:34.142 --> 03:37.679
UH, I UPPED THE SATELLITE TIER
FROM "FAMILY CHOICE"

03:37.712 --> 03:40.114
TO "FAMILY CHOICE
PLUS OPTIMUM,"

03:40.148 --> 03:42.984
THE ONE WITH
THE TENNIS CHANNEL.

03:43.017 --> 03:44.352
HMM.

03:44.385 --> 03:45.653
MOMMY,
HOLD STILL.

03:45.687 --> 03:47.155
WHOA!
WHOA, WHOA.

03:47.188 --> 03:48.556
WHOA, WHOA, WHOA, WHOA.
OKAY. GO PLAY.

03:48.590 --> 03:51.426
BEEP, BEEP, BEEP!
BE‐BOOP!

03:53.061 --> 03:55.530
I THINK TODAY I'LL TAKE
BY THE TV,

03:55.563 --> 03:56.931
MAYBE WATCH WIMBLEDON?

03:56.965 --> 03:58.867
THANKS, JILL.
THIS IS ALL...

04:02.170 --> 04:03.338
GOOD WORK.

04:03.371 --> 04:05.740
YOU ‐‐ YOU MADE NICE.

04:08.042 --> 04:10.879
ALSO, UM, ANDY AND I
ARE AT THE ROOM

04:10.912 --> 04:13.014
AT THE TOP
OF THE STAIRS.

04:13.047 --> 04:16.351
IN THE SAME ROOM TOGETHER ‐‐
THE TWO OF US.

04:16.384 --> 04:17.785
YEAH.
THAT'S A THING.

04:17.819 --> 04:19.220
THAT'S US ‐‐
OUTED.

04:19.254 --> 04:20.255
NANCE?

04:20.288 --> 04:22.156
DO YOU HEAR ME?

04:22.190 --> 04:24.325
NANCE? NANCE?!

04:26.127 --> 04:27.228
Silas: MOM?

04:28.596 --> 04:30.398
OH, SHIT.

04:30.431 --> 04:32.133
I THINK
THE BULLET'S MOVING.

04:32.166 --> 04:35.770
WHERE'S SHANE?

04:37.705 --> 04:41.175
UNFORTUNATELY,
FOR MY RETIREMENT,

04:41.209 --> 04:43.278
SHARES OF YOUR HEDGE FUND
COULDN'T BUY ME LUNCH

04:43.311 --> 04:44.746
WITH A DENTED HOOKER.

04:44.779 --> 04:46.347
WHAT ARE YOU TALKING ABOUT?
THIS IS A HEALTHY FUND.

04:46.381 --> 04:47.549
WE'RE LOOKING
AT EMERGING MARKETS.

04:47.582 --> 04:48.683
TOO MANY WORDS.

04:48.716 --> 04:52.220
YOUR FUND'S
A SINKING SHITSTONE.

04:52.253 --> 04:55.156
YOUR SHAREHOLDERS MIGHT
NOT BE ABLE TO ADD AND SUBTRACT,

04:55.189 --> 04:56.491
BUT THIS IS THE S. E. C.

04:56.524 --> 04:59.027
SO YOU CANNOT BURN MY TOAST
AND TELL ME IT'S JESUS!

05:00.061 --> 05:02.931
PLAN "A" ‐‐
YOU'RE FIRED, HE'S FIRED.

05:02.964 --> 05:04.399
BUT WE DON'T PROSECUTE.

05:04.432 --> 05:05.733
IF YOU SIGN THE FUND
OVER TO US,

05:05.767 --> 05:09.404
WE FIND NEW LEADERSHIP
AND SELL 51% TO CHINA.

05:09.437 --> 05:10.538
PLAN "B"?

05:10.572 --> 05:11.906
WE ALL GO DOWN
HOLDING HANDS.

05:11.940 --> 05:13.808
WHAT KIND OF SEVERANCE
YOU OFFERING?

05:13.841 --> 05:15.410
YOU CAN
KEEP YOUR DICKS.

05:15.443 --> 05:16.611
WHERE DO I SIGN?

05:16.644 --> 05:18.213
Whit: I GAVE 18 YEARS
TO THIS PLACE.

05:18.246 --> 05:20.415
THIS IS BULLSHIT!

05:20.448 --> 05:21.616
[ SIGHS ]
YES, WHIT.

05:21.649 --> 05:23.151
IT IS ALL
CACA BULLSHIT.

05:23.184 --> 05:24.152
RIGHT, MELNICK?

05:24.185 --> 05:25.119
SEE,
ALL MY LIFE,

05:25.153 --> 05:26.621
I WANTED TO BE
ONE OF THE BIG BOYS.

05:26.654 --> 05:29.757
BUFFETT,
ICAHN...WILSON.

05:29.791 --> 05:31.926
AND NOW HERE I AM,
TOP OF THE PYRAMID.

05:31.960 --> 05:34.362
BUT WHAT I THOUGHT
WAS A GAME OF FINESSE

05:34.395 --> 05:35.897
TURNS OUT TO BE
ONE ENDLESS

05:35.930 --> 05:38.900
ASS‐TO‐MOUTH HUMAN CENTIPEDE
OF GOVERNMENT AND BUSINESS

05:38.933 --> 05:41.803
THAT'S GONNA SUCK THIS COUNTRY
BACK TO THE STONE AGE.

05:41.836 --> 05:43.938
MY LIPS ARE CHAPPED.
MY ASSHOLE BURNS.

05:43.972 --> 05:46.541
YOU WANT TO SELL OUR CORPSE
TO CHARLIE CHAN?

05:46.574 --> 05:48.109
[ SCOFFS ]
YOU BE MY GUEST.

05:48.142 --> 05:50.478
I'M OUT OF THE GAME.
YOU COMING, WHIT?

05:50.511 --> 05:52.614
DUDE,
I'M RENOVATING MY KITCHEN.

05:52.647 --> 05:54.282
"WHIT TILLERMAN."

05:54.315 --> 05:56.284
W‐WAIT A MINUTE!
NO, NO, NO, NO.
WE'RE GOOD.

05:56.317 --> 05:57.485
WE'RE GOOD.

05:57.518 --> 05:59.087
CHIN UP, TILLERMAN.

05:59.120 --> 06:02.156
NOTHING LIKE A GOOD CRY
AFTER A TOUGH SHIT.

06:02.190 --> 06:03.491
[ DOOR OPENS ]

06:03.524 --> 06:05.059
WHAT JUST HAPPENED?
DID YOU JUST...

06:05.093 --> 06:07.028
[ DOOR CLOSES ]
AM I ON FOOD STAMPS?

06:07.061 --> 06:08.162
FUCK NO.

06:08.196 --> 06:12.333
YOU WAIT 30 SECONDS
AND THEN GET YOUR COAT.

06:14.802 --> 06:17.939
Silas: LOOKS LIKE HE
NETFLIXED A DOCUSERIES

06:17.972 --> 06:21.075
ABOUT THESE TWO SURFERS
WHO CUT THEMSELVES

06:21.109 --> 06:23.811
AND THEN FUCK UNDERWATER
IN A CAGE

06:23.845 --> 06:25.480
SURROUNDED BY SHARKS.

06:25.513 --> 06:27.682
CALLED..."BLOODFUCKERS."

06:27.715 --> 06:28.816
[ LAUGHS ]

06:28.850 --> 06:31.085
UM,
THEN HE GOOGLE‐MAPPED

06:31.119 --> 06:32.754
AN ADDRESS
IN PENNSYLVANIA DUTCH COUNTRY.

06:32.787 --> 06:34.155
OKAY, OKAY.

06:34.188 --> 06:35.490
IT'S RINGING.

06:35.523 --> 06:38.092
[ CELLPHONE VIBRATING ]

06:38.126 --> 06:39.027
[ SIGHS ]

06:39.060 --> 06:41.029
TELL ME
WHAT'S GOING ON ALREADY.

06:41.062 --> 06:42.030
[ SIGHS ]

06:42.063 --> 06:45.800
YOUR BROTHER
IS GOING AFTER THE SHOOTER.

06:45.833 --> 06:49.003
THE SHOOTER WHO SHOT ME,
WHOEVER THAT IS.

06:49.037 --> 06:50.338
[ SIGHS ]

06:50.371 --> 06:51.506
WELL...

06:51.539 --> 06:53.107
AT LEAST HE HAS TRAINING.

06:53.141 --> 06:54.842
WHAT?

06:54.876 --> 06:55.910
UM...

06:55.944 --> 06:57.946
HE SORT OF
JOINED THE POLICE ACADEMY.

06:57.979 --> 07:01.716
OKAY, EVERYBODY NEEDS TO
STOP KEEPING THINGS FROM ME

07:01.749 --> 07:03.318
THAT I NEED TO KNOW.

07:03.351 --> 07:05.086
I AM NOT A CANTALOUPE.

07:05.119 --> 07:09.090
MY POINT IS,
HE HAS ACQUIRED SOME NEW SKILLS.

07:09.123 --> 07:11.326
WH‐‐ LIKE WHAT?
DOES HE HAVE A GUN?

07:12.660 --> 07:14.329
TIM SCOTTSON.

07:14.362 --> 07:16.731
ISN'T THAT PETER'S KID?

07:16.764 --> 07:19.167
YOU GOT TO BE
KIDDING ME.

07:20.835 --> 07:21.803
PRINT THAT ADDRESS.

07:21.836 --> 07:24.739
YOU'RE DRIVING.

07:24.772 --> 07:26.541
LET'S GO, 'WITCHES!

07:26.574 --> 07:27.675
WHOO, WHOO!

07:27.709 --> 07:29.444
Andy: OKAY, LADIES.

07:29.477 --> 07:30.979
FRIENDLY REMINDER.

07:31.012 --> 07:34.682
OBSERVE THE OVAL,
THE EGG, L'OEUF, LOVE.

07:34.716 --> 07:36.918
THE FRENCH
CALL THE EGG "LOVE."

07:36.951 --> 07:39.087
SO SHALL WE.
EMBODY THAT SPIRIT.

07:39.120 --> 07:41.389
KEEP IT CLEAN.
ELBOWS TUCKED.

07:41.422 --> 07:42.657
A LOT OF MOMS OUT THERE.

07:42.690 --> 07:44.025
OH, COME ON!

07:44.058 --> 07:46.661
SLIT THEIR THROATS
AND BREAK THEIR HEARTS!

07:46.694 --> 07:48.029
WE WANT BLOOD!

07:48.062 --> 07:51.399
TEAMWORK, HEAVY EYE CONTACT,
GOOD JUDGMENT.

07:51.432 --> 07:53.134
WE WANT BLOOD!

07:53.167 --> 07:54.035
COME ON!

07:54.068 --> 07:57.138
IS HE DRUNK?
NO. JUST COMPETITIVE.

07:57.171 --> 07:58.673
JILL.
SCOTT.

07:58.706 --> 08:00.375
DIDN'T THINK
YOU'D BE HERE.

08:00.408 --> 08:01.709
DIDN'T THINK
YOU'D FUCK A GUY

08:01.743 --> 08:03.912
IN THE MIDDLE
OF MY COMMITMENT PLEDGE.

08:05.647 --> 08:07.448
OUR OLD COACH
HAD A WOODEN NICKEL

08:07.482 --> 08:08.883
WE COULD RUB
FOR GOOD LUCK.

08:08.917 --> 08:10.552
AND THEN
SHE RESIGNED IN SHAME.

08:10.585 --> 08:11.553
OKAY. BRING IT IN.

08:11.586 --> 08:14.422
DAP. DAP. DAP. DAP.

08:14.455 --> 08:17.559
DREAD MENACE,
LOOKING AT YOU

08:17.592 --> 08:18.560
FOR SOME LEADERSHIP.

08:18.593 --> 08:19.761
YOU TWO,
SHAY‐LA‐VIE.

08:19.794 --> 08:20.762
ABRACADEBRA.

08:20.795 --> 08:22.397
YOU SHAT ON MY TROTH.

08:22.430 --> 08:24.699
MM.
IT WAS A NICE TROTH.

08:24.732 --> 08:26.768
BUT YOU HAD YOUR INDIA.

08:26.801 --> 08:28.670
ANDY'S MY INDIA.

08:28.703 --> 08:30.638
I'M SURE
HE WAS A GREAT LAY.

08:30.672 --> 08:32.707
BUT HE'S NOT
STEALING MY KIDS.

08:32.740 --> 08:34.042
Man on P. A. system:
<i>PLAYERS TO THE MARK.</i>

08:34.075 --> 08:35.677
BRING THE PAIN!
LET'S GO!

08:35.710 --> 08:37.679
[ SHOUTS ]

08:37.712 --> 08:39.113
[ WHISTLE CHIRPS ]

08:39.147 --> 08:40.248
GO, GO, GO!

08:40.281 --> 08:43.151
[ CHEERING ]

08:48.656 --> 08:50.358
WHOO!

08:53.461 --> 08:54.762
HO!

08:55.763 --> 08:57.799
DREAD MENACE!

08:57.832 --> 09:01.469
WHOO!
THAT'S MY GIRL!
OW! MY HAIR TIE!

09:01.502 --> 09:03.471
NEXT TIME,
I TAKE YOUR TAMPON!

09:03.504 --> 09:05.039
COACH!

09:05.073 --> 09:06.641
YEAH. GOTCHA.
TAKE A SEAT, DREAD MENACE.

09:06.674 --> 09:07.642
YOU'RE TOO ROUGH.

09:07.675 --> 09:09.277
YOU CALL THAT ROUGH?

09:09.310 --> 09:10.812
THAT WAS A VALENTINE.

09:10.845 --> 09:12.013
OH, COME ON, COACH!

09:12.046 --> 09:14.082
YOU CAN'T
BENCH THE DREAD!

09:14.115 --> 09:15.083
WHO'S GONNA BLOCK?

09:15.116 --> 09:17.285
Scott:
BAD COACHING DECISION!

09:17.318 --> 09:20.488
BAD COACHING DECISION!

09:20.521 --> 09:22.624
COME ON!

09:22.657 --> 09:24.192
TAKE A SEAT.

09:24.225 --> 09:25.293
[ GROANING ]

09:25.326 --> 09:27.629
OUR OLD COACH
WOULD HAVE LET HER BACK IN.

09:27.662 --> 09:29.797
FINE.
SIT OUT YOUR PENALTY.

09:29.831 --> 09:32.400
I'LL GIVE YOU
ONE MORE CHANCE.

09:32.433 --> 09:33.668
YEAH, THAT'S MY GIRL!

09:33.701 --> 09:36.271
WHOO‐HOO‐HOO!

09:36.304 --> 09:37.772
[ WHISTLE BLOWS ]

09:37.805 --> 09:39.440
[ GIRLS GRUNTING ]

09:48.182 --> 09:49.551
AAH!

09:49.584 --> 09:50.818
OOH! NICE!

09:50.852 --> 09:53.421
DREAD MENACE!
[ WHISTLE CHIRPS ]

09:53.454 --> 09:55.189
OKAY, OKAY.
NOW YOU'RE DONE.

09:55.223 --> 10:00.295
TIM SCOTTSON,
LITTLE RED‐HEADED TWERP.

10:00.328 --> 10:01.829
HE WASN'T EVEN
ON MY LIST.

10:01.863 --> 10:03.531
I HAD GUILLERMO.
GUILLERMO.

10:03.565 --> 10:06.801
GUILLERMO.
I HAD GUILLERMO, TOO.

10:06.834 --> 10:09.871
HEY.
A&W RESTAURANT UP AHEAD.

10:09.904 --> 10:11.506
ROOT BEER FROM THE TAP.

10:11.539 --> 10:12.774
YEAH,
WE'RE NOT STOPPING.

10:12.807 --> 10:14.342
COME ON.
IT'LL TAKE 10 MINUTES.

10:14.375 --> 10:17.812
SILAS, YOUR BROTHER IS ABOUT
TO KILL SOMEONE...ELSE.

10:17.845 --> 10:20.415
HE'S NOT GONNA KILL HIM.

10:20.448 --> 10:22.450
TOO SMART FOR THAT.

10:22.483 --> 10:24.252
TORTURE, MAYBE.

10:24.285 --> 10:25.520
[ GROANS ]

10:25.553 --> 10:26.621
MEDIEVAL SHIT ‐‐

10:26.654 --> 10:28.256
SPANISH DONKEY,
JUDAS CRADLE.

10:28.289 --> 10:29.190
[ SIGHS ]

10:29.224 --> 10:30.625
I'M JUST SAYING,

10:30.658 --> 10:34.429
MAYBE THIS KID
DESERVES 10 MINUTES WITH SHANE.

10:34.462 --> 10:36.331
HE FUCKING SHOT YOU.

10:39.067 --> 10:41.669
[ MID‐TEMPO MUSIC
PLAYS ON RADIO ]

10:45.801 --> 10:48.204
OH!

10:48.237 --> 10:50.239
OH!

10:50.273 --> 10:53.009
WELL, THE BAD NEWS IS,
WE LOST THE BOUT.

10:53.042 --> 10:56.312
THE GOOD NEWS IS,
EVERYONE GETS HALF A DOUGHNUT.

10:56.345 --> 10:57.280
[ ALL GROAN ]

10:57.313 --> 10:59.549
YOU SHOULD HAVE
LET HER PLAY.

10:59.582 --> 11:00.850
NOW WE'RE UNDER .500.

11:00.883 --> 11:02.818
GOODBYE, PLAYOFFS.

11:02.852 --> 11:04.120
HELLO, FAILURE.

11:04.153 --> 11:06.522
IT'S JUST A GAME.

11:06.556 --> 11:08.758
THERE ARE NO GAMES
WHERE WE COME FROM.

11:08.791 --> 11:10.159
YOU COME FROM OAKLAND.

11:10.193 --> 11:11.828
WE COME FROM
JUST SOUTH OF OAKLAND!

11:11.861 --> 11:14.063
HELL?
MAYBE YOU'VE HEARD OF IT?

11:14.096 --> 11:15.097
Scott: HEY, HEY.

11:15.131 --> 11:16.365
WHO WANTS TO
HIT THE DINER?

11:16.399 --> 11:18.634
ENTERPRISE
UPGRADED ME TO A SEBRING.

11:18.668 --> 11:19.635
Twins: SHOTGUN!

11:19.669 --> 11:20.970
MOM, YOU COMING?

11:21.003 --> 11:22.672
Jill: NAH, I'M GONNA
HANG BACK WITH ANDY.

11:22.705 --> 11:24.507
YOU GUYS GO.

11:25.975 --> 11:27.109
THEY'RE SWEET.

11:27.143 --> 11:29.378
AW, YOU'LL GET THEM
NEXT TIME.

11:29.412 --> 11:30.379
HMM.

11:30.413 --> 11:33.449
YOU'RE GREAT
WITH THE GIRLS. REALLY.

11:33.482 --> 11:34.851
OH.

11:34.884 --> 11:39.021
OUR OLD COACH MADE US POPSICLES
OUT OF Hi‐C FRUIT PUNCH.

11:42.158 --> 11:44.160
WAS YOUR MOM
THE OLD COACH?

11:45.328 --> 11:46.729
[ SOBS ]

11:54.403 --> 11:56.439
OH.

11:56.472 --> 11:57.440
HI.

11:57.473 --> 11:58.441
HI.

11:58.474 --> 11:59.809
CAN I HELP YOU OR...

11:59.842 --> 12:00.943
YEAH.

12:00.977 --> 12:02.678
WE'RE OLD FRIENDS
OF TIM'S,

12:02.712 --> 12:05.548
AND WE WERE JUST
PASSING THROUGH ON OUR
WAY TO GETTYSBURG,

12:05.581 --> 12:07.683
AND WE WERE JUST ‐‐

12:07.717 --> 12:09.418
IS HE HERE? TIM?

12:09.452 --> 12:10.486
TIMMY?

12:10.520 --> 12:11.954
TIMOTH...Y?

12:11.988 --> 12:15.525
OH, I'M AFRAID NOT,
BUT HE SHOULD BE BACK SOON.

12:15.558 --> 12:16.526
I'M TULA.

12:16.559 --> 12:17.894
NANCY.
MIKE.

12:17.927 --> 12:20.630
UM, DO YOU ‐‐
DO YOU GUYS WANT TO COME IN?

12:20.663 --> 12:22.932
I MEAN, HE SHOULD BE BACK
FROM WORK ANY MINUTE.

12:22.965 --> 12:24.167
I HAVE WATER.

12:34.477 --> 12:36.779
SO, UH...

12:36.812 --> 12:38.948
WHAT'S THAT SMELL?

12:38.981 --> 12:40.550
ARE YOU BAKING A PIE?

12:40.583 --> 12:41.851
I DON'T THINK SO.

12:41.884 --> 12:43.920
SO,
HOW DID YOU TWO MEET?

12:43.953 --> 12:46.722
WELL, HE SAVED ME
FROM THE RAPE BARN

12:46.756 --> 12:49.559
BACK WHEN IT WAS
STILL MADE OF WOOD.

12:49.592 --> 12:50.927
MM.

12:50.960 --> 12:52.962
OH.
DID YOU SEE THIS?

12:52.995 --> 12:54.564
THIS WAS TIM'S DAD'S.

12:54.597 --> 12:56.098
TIM LOST HIM
AT AN EARLY AGE.

12:56.132 --> 12:59.035
SO SORRY TO HEAR THAT.

12:59.068 --> 13:01.437
YEAH.
THAT'LL MESS A KID UP.

13:01.470 --> 13:02.305
I KNOW.

13:02.338 --> 13:04.173
HE'S LUCKY HE TURNED OUT
SO FINE.

13:04.207 --> 13:07.643
HIS MOM, THOUGH ‐‐
SHE'S A PSYCHO.

13:07.677 --> 13:10.680
TIM SURE
HAS A LOT OF SHOES.

13:10.713 --> 13:12.448
OH,
THOSE AREN'T SHOES.

13:12.481 --> 13:13.850
THOSE ARE HIS RABBITS.

13:13.883 --> 13:16.252
WELL, THEY WERE
WHEN THEY WERE ALIVE.

13:16.285 --> 13:18.955
I TOLD HIM THEY SHOULDN'T
BAKE IN THE SUN LIKE THAT,

13:18.988 --> 13:20.857
BUT, YOU KNOW,
HE'S NOT A LISTENER.

13:20.890 --> 13:21.858
UH, THERE'S 12.

13:21.891 --> 13:23.593
THEY'RE ALL NAMED PETER.

13:23.626 --> 13:25.361
JUST, UM,
DON'T PET THEM.

13:25.394 --> 13:27.663
HE ‐‐
HE DOESN'T LIKE THAT.

13:27.697 --> 13:29.365
HE NAMED THEM ALL PETER?

13:29.398 --> 13:32.101
YOU KNOW,
LIKE PETER THE RABBIT?

13:32.134 --> 13:34.704
HOLD, PLEASE. NEED REST.

13:34.737 --> 13:37.373
HAS ANYONE
BEEN AROUND TODAY?

13:37.406 --> 13:40.443
ANYONE AT ALL?
SOMEONE NAMED SHANE?

13:40.476 --> 13:41.844
WELL, NO.

13:41.878 --> 13:44.647
NO,
NOT THAT I CAN SAY.

13:44.680 --> 13:48.784
ALTHOUGH ONE OF TIMOTHY'S
NEW FRIENDS STOPPED BY EARLIER,

13:48.818 --> 13:50.753
UH,
TO GO HUNTING WITH HIM.

13:50.786 --> 13:52.755
I LET HIM
BORROW TIM'S GUN.

13:53.856 --> 13:55.958
THAT'S WEIRD.

13:57.627 --> 13:58.961
THAT IS WEIRD.

13:58.995 --> 14:00.563
TIM'S GUN.

14:00.596 --> 14:02.331
TIM'S GUN.

14:02.365 --> 14:06.035
"PROJECT RUNWAY."

14:06.068 --> 14:08.237
ANYWAY,
IT'S DEER SEASON,

14:08.271 --> 14:10.439
AND HE ‐‐
HE PROMISED ME THE RIB MEAT.

14:10.473 --> 14:13.643
SO, THIS GUY THAT CAME BY,
YOU DON'T KNOW HIM AT ALL?

14:13.676 --> 14:15.545
WELL,
HE JUST LOOKED LIKE

14:15.578 --> 14:18.714
ALL OF TIM'S OTHER
NON‐ALBINO FRIENDS.

14:18.748 --> 14:20.816
YOU KNOW,
KIND OF SHIFTY, UH,

14:20.850 --> 14:24.854
QUIET,
DEAD EYES, TRUSTWORTHY.

14:24.887 --> 14:26.222
MM.

14:26.255 --> 14:27.990
I‐I'M SORRY.
WHAT TIME DID YOU SAY IT WAS?

14:28.024 --> 14:28.991
IT'S STRANGE.

14:29.025 --> 14:30.893
H‐HE SHOULD BE HOME BY NOW.

14:30.927 --> 14:32.161
H‐HE'S NEVER LATE.

14:32.195 --> 14:34.363
UH,
I THINK WE SHOULD GET GOING.

14:34.397 --> 14:37.800
HOW DID YOU SAY
THAT YOU KNEW TIMOTHY AGAIN?

14:37.834 --> 14:39.602
HE SHOT HER
IN THE HEAD.

14:40.469 --> 14:41.470
SILAS!

14:41.504 --> 14:43.973
TRIED TO KILL HER
TWO MONTHS AGO.

14:44.006 --> 14:45.208
COME ON, MOM.

14:58.421 --> 15:02.825
I DON'T KNOW
IF I CAN DO THIS ANYMORE.

15:02.859 --> 15:05.261
WHERE'D YOU SAY
HE WORKED AGAIN?

15:09.866 --> 15:11.634
SORRY I BENCHED YOU.

15:11.667 --> 15:12.869
SORRY WE LOST.

15:12.902 --> 15:14.837
WHAT IS THIS?

15:14.871 --> 15:16.339
MY MEA CULPA.

15:16.372 --> 15:20.710
LIMITED‐EDITION COPY
OF ROLLER GIRL CINEMATIC OPUS

15:20.743 --> 15:21.978
"KANSAS CITY BOMBER."

15:22.011 --> 15:23.746
TURN IT OVER.
IT'S SIGNED.

15:23.779 --> 15:25.848
"DEAR TAYLOR,
FOLLOW YOUR DREAMS,

15:25.882 --> 15:27.116
"BE NICE TO ANDY.

15:27.149 --> 15:29.452
"HE'S NOT TRYING
TO REPLACE YOUR FATHER.

15:29.485 --> 15:30.987
RAQUEL WELCH."

15:31.020 --> 15:32.255
[ SCOFFS ]

15:32.288 --> 15:34.123
WHAT?
WHAT'S THE MATTER?

15:34.156 --> 15:36.993
I'M NOT TAYLOR.
I'M SHAYLA.

15:37.026 --> 15:38.961
DUH. NO DREADLOCK.

15:38.995 --> 15:40.630
TAYLOR'S
IN THE KITCHEN.

15:42.865 --> 15:45.101
WOW.

15:45.134 --> 15:47.103
YOU'RE BOTH FEELING
KIND OF DARK TODAY, HUH?

15:47.136 --> 15:49.906
WHAT YOU MAKING THERE,
NUMBER TWO?

15:49.939 --> 15:52.441
I'M BAKING YOUR SHOES.

15:52.475 --> 15:53.476
WHAT?

15:53.509 --> 15:55.378
WHEN WE LOSE,
WE BURN YOUR SHOES.

15:55.411 --> 15:56.913
Both: WHEN WE LOSE,
WE BURN YOUR SHOES.

15:56.946 --> 15:59.382
WHEN WE LOSE,
WE BURN YOUR SHOES.

15:59.415 --> 16:00.283
Andy: OH, SHIT!

16:00.316 --> 16:01.617
SHAYLA,
WHERE ‐‐ WHERE ‐‐

16:01.651 --> 16:02.952
WHERE'D YOUR MOTHER
MOVE THE OVEN MITTS TO?

16:02.985 --> 16:04.720
I'M NOT SHAYLA.
I'M TAYLOR.

16:04.754 --> 16:06.389
WELL, WHO'S WHO?
I CAN'T TELL.

16:06.422 --> 16:07.423
WHO'S THE GOOD TWIN?

16:10.393 --> 16:11.394
I AM.

16:14.864 --> 16:16.232
NOT COOL!

16:16.265 --> 16:17.066
NOT COOL!

16:17.099 --> 16:18.835
I HAVE EIGHT TOES!

16:18.868 --> 16:21.537
FOOTWEAR
IS SUPER‐SELECTIVE FOR ME!

16:21.571 --> 16:23.339
HEY. HERE'S 50 BUCKS.

16:23.372 --> 16:26.242
TAKE THEM TO THE CLAIRE'S
AT THE MALL.

16:26.275 --> 16:28.811
BUY THEM EARRINGS
OR SOMETHING.

16:28.845 --> 16:30.613
JUST
BUY THEIR LOVE.

16:30.646 --> 16:33.115
YOU'RE ANDY.
YOU CAN DO THIS.

16:35.718 --> 16:37.787
OKAY. I'M ON IT.

16:37.820 --> 16:42.191
SIX‐INCH
OR FOOT...LONG?

16:43.459 --> 16:46.095
JUST MAKE ME A SANDWICH.

16:47.396 --> 16:50.666
YOU'RE SUPPOSED TO TELL HER
ABOUT THE SPECIALS, TIMMY.

16:50.700 --> 16:52.702
[ SIGHS ] UH...

16:52.735 --> 16:54.170
YOU GET A ‐‐
LOUDER.

16:54.203 --> 16:56.072
YOU'RE NOT GOING HOME
UNTIL YOU GET THIS RIGHT.

16:56.105 --> 16:59.408
UM, YOU...GET
A FREE MEDIUM SODA

16:59.442 --> 17:03.546
IF YOU BUY
ANY TWO FLATBREADS.

17:05.882 --> 17:07.750
WHAT KIND OF MEAT?

17:07.783 --> 17:09.452
DOESN'T MATTER.

17:09.485 --> 17:10.319
TURKEY.

17:10.353 --> 17:12.655
CAN'T TASTE ANYTHING
ANYWAY.

17:12.688 --> 17:13.823
UM...

17:13.856 --> 17:15.424
VEGGIES?

17:15.458 --> 17:16.893
LOAD ME UP.

17:16.926 --> 17:18.761
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

17:18.794 --> 17:22.265
IS THAT HOW WE DO LETTUCE,
SCOTTSON?

17:22.298 --> 17:25.668
UM, CHEESE?

17:25.701 --> 17:27.537
WHATEVER.

17:27.570 --> 17:28.971
[ SIGHS ] AVOCADO?

17:29.005 --> 17:31.174
YOU'RE SUPPOSED TO
LET THEM KNOW THAT'S EXTRA.

17:31.207 --> 17:33.276
WILL YOU SHUT UP?
HE'S TRYING.

17:37.113 --> 17:39.048
DO YOU WANT THE AVOCADO?
NO. MOVE ON.

17:39.081 --> 17:41.284
LIGHT SAUCE
OR FULL FLAVOR?

17:41.317 --> 17:43.119
SURPRISE ME.

17:49.578 --> 17:53.415
THAT'LL BE $4.95.

17:56.285 --> 17:59.388
GET IN MY CAR
BEFORE I CALL YOUR MOTHER.

18:03.525 --> 18:05.327
COME ON, MAN.
GIVE ME A HINT.

18:05.361 --> 18:07.129
ANOTHER HEDGE FUND?
PRIVATE EQUITY?

18:07.162 --> 18:08.564
UH,
WE STARTING OUR OWN FIRM?

18:08.597 --> 18:10.099
NAH,
THAT'S CHUMP CHANGE.

18:10.132 --> 18:11.533
YOU'RE THINKING
LIKE A MOUSE.

18:11.567 --> 18:12.534
THINK LIKE A KING.

18:12.568 --> 18:14.003
HELLO, MR. DOUG.

18:14.036 --> 18:15.104
HOLA, MIGUEL.

18:15.137 --> 18:16.505
IT'S MARIA.

18:16.538 --> 18:17.940
[ CHUCKLES ]
I DON'T KNOW, MAN.

18:17.973 --> 18:18.941
I‐I GIVE UP.

18:18.974 --> 18:20.743
AFTER YOU.

18:20.776 --> 18:22.745
[ CHUCKLES ]

18:27.016 --> 18:28.083
PUSH THE RED
BLINKING LIGHT.

18:32.421 --> 18:34.990
[ <i>BEEP</i>]
Maria: <i>HELLO.</i>

18:35.024 --> 18:37.793
<i>YOU HAVE REACHED THE</i>
<i>DOUGLAS S. WILSON FOUNDATION,</i>

18:37.826 --> 18:42.798
<i>A 501(c)3</i>
<i>NONPROFIT ORGANIZATION.</i>

18:42.831 --> 18:43.966
[ <i>BEEP</i>]

18:43.999 --> 18:45.534
WE'RE STARTING A CHARITY?
THAT DOES WHAT?

18:45.567 --> 18:47.937
I DON'T KNOW,
BUT LAST WEEK,

18:47.970 --> 18:51.273
VEHEMENT DONATED
A BUTTLOAD OF MONEY TO IT.

18:51.307 --> 18:52.274
HOLY SHIT.

18:52.308 --> 18:53.609
CHARITIES?

18:53.642 --> 18:53.976
YES!

18:54.009 --> 18:56.812
[ LAUGHS ]

19:02.151 --> 19:08.123
MY BROTHER TOOK YOUR GUN,
AND WE DON'T KNOW WHERE HE IS.

19:08.157 --> 19:09.603
AND HE'S KILLED BEFORE.

19:09.636 --> 19:11.839
SO...

19:11.872 --> 19:13.173
IF I WERE YOU,

19:13.207 --> 19:14.475
I WOULD KEEP YOUR HEAD
BELOW THE WINDOWS.

19:16.777 --> 19:21.148
SHANE? IT'S MOM!

19:21.181 --> 19:22.816
CAN WE TALK

19:22.850 --> 19:26.820
BEFORE YOU DO SOMETHING
INCREDIBLY STUPID?

19:29.490 --> 19:32.259
Tim: HEY.
CHECK THIS OUT.

19:32.292 --> 19:35.295
BITCHES BE CRAZY,
HUH?

19:36.697 --> 19:39.900
I NEED SOME AIR.

19:45.772 --> 19:46.974
[ SIGHS ]

19:47.007 --> 19:49.176
[ CAR DOOR CLOSES ]

19:49.209 --> 19:52.179
OKAY.
WHY ARE YOU HERE?

19:52.212 --> 19:54.615
I'M A SANDWICH ARTIST.

19:54.648 --> 19:58.152
YOU ARE A 19‐YEAR‐OLD
FROM AGRESTIC, CALIFORNIA.

19:58.185 --> 20:00.020
YOU SHOULD BE IN COLLEGE.

20:00.053 --> 20:01.321
THIS IS FREAKTOWN.

20:01.355 --> 20:03.323
WHAT ARE
YOU DOING HERE?

20:03.357 --> 20:05.526
YOU'RE SUPPOSED TO BE DEAD.

20:05.559 --> 20:07.461
OR AT LEAST VEGETATIVE.

20:07.494 --> 20:10.430
YEAH, WELL,
I'M A WALKING MIRACLE.

20:10.464 --> 20:13.167
AND I'M TRYING
TO PROTECT YOU.

20:13.200 --> 20:14.268
OH.

20:14.301 --> 20:16.270
I CAN TAKE CARE
OF MYSELF.

20:16.303 --> 20:18.071
MY DAD
TAUGHT ME INDEPENDENCE.

20:18.105 --> 20:19.206
OH, NO. WAIT.

20:19.239 --> 20:21.008
HE ENDED UP
IN A DRAIN PIPE.

20:21.041 --> 20:24.144
I HEARD THAT.

20:24.178 --> 20:25.412
YOU KNOW,
I HOPE ONE DAY

20:25.445 --> 20:27.181
SOMEONE GIVES YOU
SOME FRESH ROSES

20:27.214 --> 20:29.283
AND YOU SNEEZE
AND THE BULLET IN YOUR BRAIN

20:29.316 --> 20:31.518
MOVES 1/8 INCH
TO THE RIGHT

20:31.552 --> 20:34.655
AND YOU SEE BLUE
AND YOU SMELL CHEESE

20:34.688 --> 20:35.722
AND YOU DIE.

20:38.158 --> 20:42.729
YOUR FATHER
WAS A COMPLICATED MAN.

20:42.763 --> 20:44.498
HE WAS A HERO.

20:44.531 --> 20:45.999
I DIDN'T EVEN KILL HIM.

20:46.033 --> 20:48.068
IT WAS THE ARMENIANS
AND HEYLIA.

20:48.101 --> 20:49.269
DO YOUR HOMEWORK.

20:49.303 --> 20:51.205
YOU CAN'T EVEN
SAY YOU'RE SORRY!

20:51.238 --> 20:52.339
[ CAR DOOR OPENS ]

20:52.372 --> 20:53.507
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

20:53.540 --> 20:55.142
[ CAR DOOR CLOSES, OPENS ]

20:55.175 --> 20:56.176
GET OUT OF THE CAR.

20:56.210 --> 20:57.444
UH, NO.

20:57.478 --> 20:58.779
T‐THAT RIFLE
HAS A 1/2‐MILE RANGE ON IT.

21:02.716 --> 21:06.019
Tim: OKAY.
ALL RIGHT. ALL RIGHT.

21:06.053 --> 21:09.256
LOOK,
YOU NEED TO FIX YOUR LIFE.

21:09.289 --> 21:11.792
IT SUCKS YOU HAD TO GROW UP
WITHOUT A DAD.

21:11.825 --> 21:15.395
BUT THAT IS NOT AN EXCUSE
TO ACT LIKE A PSYCHOPATH.

21:15.429 --> 21:17.397
ARE YOU LISTENING,
SHANE?!

21:17.431 --> 21:20.267
SHOOTING ME DID NOT
SOLVE YOUR PROBLEMS.

21:20.300 --> 21:22.369
PLEASE!
I HAVE A GIRLFRIEND.

21:22.402 --> 21:23.670
HOW ABOUT THAT?

21:23.704 --> 21:25.839
I TOLD HER ABOUT
THE ASSASSINATION ATTEMPT.

21:25.873 --> 21:26.974
SHE WAS PRETTY MAD.

21:27.007 --> 21:28.876
SHE MIGHT NOT
BE THERE ANYMORE.

21:28.909 --> 21:30.077
I‐I NEED TO GET HOME.

21:30.110 --> 21:31.879
YOU HAVE TO
PAY ATTENTION, OKAY?

21:31.912 --> 21:34.948
I CAN'T BE RESPONSIBLE
FOR ANOTHER MESSED‐UP KID.

21:34.982 --> 21:36.683
UNLOCK THE DOOR.
PLEASE. OPEN.

21:36.717 --> 21:40.154
BURY THE RABBITS.
PACK UP YOUR CAR.

21:40.187 --> 21:42.289
STOP FUCKING THE AMISH.

21:42.322 --> 21:44.458
BECOME A NUTRITIONIST,
OKAY?

21:44.491 --> 21:46.260
THESE ARE MY CONDITIONS.

21:46.293 --> 21:48.095
THEN YOU CAN GET BACK
IN THE CAR,

21:48.128 --> 21:50.130
WE CAN TALK ABOUT
HOW TO FIX THIS, OKAY?

21:50.164 --> 21:51.665
OKAY.

21:51.698 --> 21:52.699
ALL RIGHT.

21:52.733 --> 21:54.201
OKAY. CAN I BORROW
SOME GAS MONEY?

21:54.234 --> 21:56.603
IF YOU GIVE ME A HUG.

21:56.637 --> 21:57.638
BITCH.

21:57.671 --> 21:59.439
YEAH, WELL...

22:10.918 --> 22:12.419
SCOTT: Andy.

22:12.452 --> 22:13.654
What the fuck
are you doing?

22:13.687 --> 22:16.390
What the fuck
is he doing here?

22:16.423 --> 22:19.460
You were supposed to
take them to the mall!

22:19.493 --> 22:21.395
Balls!
Balls to the mall!

22:21.428 --> 22:23.730
What's on your feet?
Dog socks.

22:23.764 --> 22:26.099
Textured socks for dogs.

22:26.133 --> 22:27.201
Why?

22:27.234 --> 22:28.735
I'm supposed to
return those!

22:28.769 --> 22:31.038
[ SCREAMS ]

22:33.240 --> 22:34.908
Jill: YOU WON'T EVEN
NOTICE IT ‐‐

22:34.942 --> 22:36.410
SEWING IT
RIGHT BACK IN.

22:36.443 --> 22:38.479
WHAT THE HECK
YOU DOING TO MY KID?

22:38.512 --> 22:40.080
PLEASE.
SHE STARTED IT.

22:40.113 --> 22:41.148
DON'T CUT
MY KID'S HAIR.

22:41.181 --> 22:42.416
IT'S HER HAIR.

22:42.449 --> 22:44.384
WHOA, WHAT'S WITH
ALL THE HOSTILITY?

22:44.418 --> 22:46.353
DID YOU LEARN NOTHING
IN INDIA?

22:46.386 --> 22:47.554
Jill: SCOTT.

22:47.588 --> 22:49.123
DAD,
BREAK HIS FACE!

22:49.156 --> 22:50.124
Shayla:
YEAH! WE WANT BLOOD!

22:50.157 --> 22:51.325
NO,
WE DON'T!

22:51.358 --> 22:52.426
Scott: COME ON.

22:52.459 --> 22:54.661
HE'S NOT GONNA FIGHT.

22:54.695 --> 22:56.130
L'OEUF. THE EGG.

22:56.163 --> 22:57.798
THE FRENCH EGG.

22:57.831 --> 22:59.366
[ SMOOCHING ]

23:01.001 --> 23:02.069
OW!
DID YOU ‐‐

23:02.102 --> 23:03.203
DAD, MAKE A FIST!

23:03.237 --> 23:05.005
DON'T YOU KNOW
HOW TO PUNCH?

23:05.038 --> 23:06.874
ANDY, HIT HIM
IN THE FACE!
NO!

23:06.907 --> 23:08.942
NO FACE!
OW! FUCKER!

23:08.976 --> 23:10.177
Taylor:
NO MORE SLAPPING!

23:10.210 --> 23:11.712
GEEZ, DAD,
YOU GOT SAND IN YOUR POOTER?

23:11.745 --> 23:12.880
HEY! NO "POOTER"!

23:12.913 --> 23:14.081
OH, GOD ‐‐

23:14.114 --> 23:15.149
WHAT ARE
YOU DOING?!

23:15.182 --> 23:18.285
DON'T ‐‐
DON'T THROW.

23:18.318 --> 23:20.754
HEY! HEY!
WE HATE YOU BOTH!

23:21.755 --> 23:23.023
GIRLS...

23:23.056 --> 23:25.025
YOU UNGRATEFUL
LITTLE SHITS!
...I AM TRYING, OKAY?

23:25.058 --> 23:27.661
YES, I ADMIT IT.
YOU THINK THE SEBRING
WAS FOR ME?

23:27.694 --> 23:29.296
I FORGED THE SIGNATURE.
WRONG!

23:29.329 --> 23:30.998
DO YOU THINK YOU'RE THE REASON
WE'RE SEPARATED?

23:31.031 --> 23:33.000
GUESS WHAT ‐‐
YOU'RE RIGHT.
COME ON.
IT'S RAQUEL WELCH.

23:33.033 --> 23:35.068
WHAT DID YOU EXPECT?
BUT THIS DIVORCE DOES NOT
GIVE YOU THE CARTE BLANCHE

23:35.102 --> 23:37.204
TO WEAR BLACK EYE SHADOW
AND GIVE UP YOUR VIRGINITY...
WHAT AM I TO HER?

23:37.237 --> 23:39.039
LIKE SHE'S GONNA RESPOND IF I
JUST PUT IT IN THE REGULAR MAIL?
...TO ETHNICS!

23:39.072 --> 23:40.374
YOU KNOW WHAT?

23:40.407 --> 23:42.109
I'M GLAD HE CUT OFF THAT
FILTHY LITTLE RAT TAIL!

23:42.142 --> 23:43.277
SCOTT?

23:43.310 --> 23:44.645
I'VE BEEN TO MUMBAI,
JUST GOT BACK,

23:44.678 --> 23:46.613
AND LITTLE GIRLS OVER THERE
ARE SELLING THEIR HAIR

23:46.647 --> 23:48.682
FOR MONEY AND THEN
POOPING IN THE RIVER!

23:48.715 --> 23:49.883
DO YOU EVEN HEAR
WHAT YOU'RE SAYING?

23:49.917 --> 23:50.951
NO. YOU KNOW WHAT?

23:50.984 --> 23:52.452
I'M NOT EVEN
CLOSE TO DONE, JILL!

23:52.486 --> 23:54.288
YOU THINK
WE WANTED TWINS?

23:54.321 --> 23:55.289
OH, SCOTT ‐‐

23:55.322 --> 23:56.757
WE WANTED ONE KID.
UNO.

23:56.790 --> 23:59.126
YOU KNOW WHAT I SAID
WHEN I SAW THE SONOGRAM?
SCOTT?

23:59.159 --> 24:01.128
"SCREW THIS.
LET'S ABORT AND GET A BOAT."

24:01.161 --> 24:04.164
GOD! I AM SAYING
VERY HORRIBLE THINGS.

24:04.198 --> 24:05.466
THIS ISN'T ME.

24:05.499 --> 24:08.068
TWINS, I APOLOGIZE.

24:08.101 --> 24:11.104
I GOT TO GO BACK TO CALCUTTA
AND GET AWAY FROM ALL THIS CRAP.

24:11.138 --> 24:12.840
YOU'LL HEAR
FROM MY LAWYER, JILL.

24:12.873 --> 24:15.409
I'LL BE BACK
IN THE FALL.

24:15.442 --> 24:20.614
IN THE MEANTIME, GIRLS...
LISTEN TO ANDY.

24:20.647 --> 24:22.583
[ DOOR OPENS ]

24:26.887 --> 24:29.189
GO TO YOUR ROOM.

24:29.223 --> 24:30.891
[ SIGHS ]

24:30.924 --> 24:32.392
[ SIGHS ]

24:32.426 --> 24:39.266
SHE LEFT US, PETER, PETER,
PETER, PETER, PETER ‐‐

24:41.401 --> 24:43.036
YOU'RE WELCOME.

24:43.070 --> 24:45.072
TIM,
PACK UP WHAT YOU NEED

24:45.105 --> 24:46.974
AND GO STRAIGHT
TO CALIFORNIA.

24:47.007 --> 24:48.342
COME ON.
NO STOPPING.

24:48.375 --> 24:50.677
DID IT HURT
GETTING SHOT?

24:50.711 --> 24:52.579
I DON'T ‐‐ I DON'T
REALLY REMEMBER, HONEY.

24:52.613 --> 24:53.747
JUST TRYING
TO PREPARE MYSELF.

24:53.780 --> 24:55.149
THEY HAVE
REALLY GOOD DOCTORS NOW.

24:55.182 --> 24:56.850
COME ON. LET'S GO.
[ KNOCK ON DOOR ]

24:58.585 --> 25:00.287
Go in the bathroom.
Go in the bathroom!

25:00.320 --> 25:01.455
Go! Go! Go!

25:02.723 --> 25:05.292
GREAT. SHE TOOK HER
FUCKING TOOTHBRUSH.

25:07.127 --> 25:08.095
WHERE IS HE?

25:08.128 --> 25:09.630
SHANE.

25:09.663 --> 25:12.800
JESUS, THIS PLACE MAKES MY SHACK
LOOK LIKE THE TAJ MAHAL.

25:12.833 --> 25:14.668
[ POLICE RADIO CHATTER ]
YEAH. GO AHEAD.

25:16.103 --> 25:18.305
MR. SCOTTSON,
WE HAVE A WARRANT.

25:18.338 --> 25:20.474
THE STATE OF CONNECTICUT
HAS PLACED YOU UNDER ARREST

25:20.507 --> 25:22.309
FOR THE ATTEMPTED MURDER
OF NANCY BOTWIN.

25:22.342 --> 25:24.745
THIS IS SERGEANT JENSEN,
OSPD, ARRESTING OFFICER,

25:24.778 --> 25:28.248
AND OFFICER THURGOOD NOTGOOD,
LOCAL JURISDICTION.

25:28.282 --> 25:29.883
UH,
HE DIDN'T DO IT.

25:29.917 --> 25:31.885
HE DIDN'T.
HE HAS AN ALIBI.

25:31.919 --> 25:33.120
ASK HIS GIRLFRIEND.

25:33.153 --> 25:35.289
HE WAS B‐BAKING
HIS GIRLFRIEND A PIE.

25:35.322 --> 25:38.058
WE HAVE THE GUN
AND THE SHELL CASINGS.

25:38.091 --> 25:39.226
AND GUESS WHAT.

25:39.259 --> 25:41.094
THE CARPET
MATCHED THE DRAPES.

25:41.128 --> 25:42.796
YOU FOUND
MY PUBIC HAIR?

25:43.897 --> 25:45.365
I'M NOT
PRESSING CHARGES.

25:45.399 --> 25:47.267
ANYTHING ABOVE MANSLAUGHTER
GOES STRAIGHT TO THE D. A.

25:47.301 --> 25:48.368
IT'S NOT YOUR CALL.

25:48.402 --> 25:49.770
MA'AM,
STEP ASIDE, PLEASE.

25:50.938 --> 25:52.473
IT'S OKAY.

25:52.506 --> 25:55.776
Jensen: MA'AM, PLEASE.

25:55.809 --> 25:57.978
[ SIREN WAILING ]

26:01.448 --> 26:03.150
YOU HAVE THE RIGHT
TO REMAIN SILENT.

26:03.183 --> 26:04.651
YOU HAVE THE RIGHT
TO AN ATTORNEY.

26:04.685 --> 26:06.920
ANYTHING YOU SAY CAN AND WILL
BE USED AGAINST YOU

26:06.954 --> 26:08.622
IN A COURT OF LAW.

26:08.655 --> 26:10.491
THESE KIDS ‐‐
THEY MAKE ONE MISTAKE,

26:10.524 --> 26:12.459
AND IT FOLLOWS THEM
THEIR WHOLE LIVES.

26:12.493 --> 26:16.096
IF CANNOT AFFORD AN ATTORNEY,
ONE WILL BE APPOINTED FOR YOU.

26:16.130 --> 26:17.564
HEY.

26:17.598 --> 26:18.899
SMILE, MOM.

26:18.932 --> 26:20.901
HE'S TRYING
TO IMPRESS YOU.

26:20.934 --> 26:22.669
[ POLICE RADIO CHATTER ]

26:27.040 --> 26:30.010
[ MID‐TEMPO MUSIC PLAYS ]

26:38.185 --> 26:40.454
♪♪ OH, NO, LOOK IN THE MIRROR ♪♪

26:40.487 --> 26:44.158
♪♪ IT'S THE FIVE‐O ♪♪

26:44.191 --> 26:46.593
♪♪ I SHOULDN'T HAVE SMOKED
SO MUCH WEED ♪♪

26:46.627 --> 26:49.196
♪♪ I SHOULDN'T HAVE DONE
SO MUCH BLOW ♪♪

26:49.229 --> 26:55.202
♪♪ DON'T YOU KNOW SOMETIMES ♪♪

26:55.235 --> 26:58.338
♪♪ THAT'S HOW I ROLL ♪♪

27:05.779 --> 27:08.282
[ SONG CONTINUES ON RADIO ]

27:08.315 --> 27:09.616
[ SIREN WAILS ]

27:09.650 --> 27:12.486
WHAT'S WITH
ALL THE COPS?

27:12.519 --> 27:13.954
DRIVE, LARRY.
DRIVE!

27:13.987 --> 27:15.622
[ ENGINE TURNS OVER ]

